{"TopicId":97154,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.9-1.10] Throttle Controlled Avionics","CreatedByName":"allista","CreatedById":99885,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-19T12:17:01Z","PageNum":44,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Bit Fiddler","CreatedById":103108,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T06:56:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou mean like this?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/O7ayf5Mssrs?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FirroSeranel","CreatedById":144343,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T07:02:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222814107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002297154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476946615\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103108\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bit Fiddler\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Bit Fiddler said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou mean like this?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaha, very close! And very badass! *grins* Was that actually you? Very nicely done if so.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bit Fiddler","CreatedById":103108,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T07:08:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nno just a random vid on youtube I saw...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSolid Rocket Boosters: \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:funds:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/Funds.png\u0022 title=\u0022:funds:\u0022\u003E400.00\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHitchHiker Crew Pod: \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:funds:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/Funds.png\u0022 title=\u0022:funds:\u0022\u003E4000.00\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe look on Bob \u0026amp; Bills face: Priceless\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FirroSeranel","CreatedById":144343,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T07:36:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/99885-allista/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002299885\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/99885-allista/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@allista\u003C/a\u003E, I\u0027m having trouble with manual controlled engine throttles.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to make a ship with ventral hover engines on Thrust, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E-style attitude engines on Maneuver, and then one main aft-facing engine for fast translational movement, kind of like the hover-carrier in Avatar.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can get everything to work but the aft engine. I have that one set to Manual Control, but when I try to move its throttle slider, it just jumps back to zero unless I also turn off vertical speed control of all kinds, which isn\u0027t what I want.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAm I doing something wrong?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"allista","CreatedById":99885,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T07:42:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222814140\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002297154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476948972\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144343\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FirroSeranel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, FirroSeranel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/99885-allista/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002299885\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/99885-allista/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@allista\u003C/a\u003E, I\u0027m having trouble with manual controlled engine throttles.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to make a ship with ventral hover engines on Thrust, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E-style attitude engines on Maneuver, and then one main aft-facing engine for fast translational movement, kind of like the hover-carrier in Avatar.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can get everything to work but the aft engine. I have that one set to Manual Control, but when I try to move its throttle slider, it just jumps back to zero unless I also turn off vertical speed control of all kinds, which isn\u0027t what I want.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAm I doing something wrong?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is another hard-to-explain design decisions: manual engines may be controlled manually, unless you use some sort of horizontal speed control (or autopilots that use it). For example, the Stop\u00A0program will\u00A0use manual engines; the Cruise, Path Navigation... anything that controls horizontal movement. So \u0022manual\u0022 engines are not so manual after all\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut, if you say that Vertical Speed/Altitude\u00A0Control has something to do, that it\u0027s probably a bug. It shouldn\u0027t.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll investigate the matter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FirroSeranel","CreatedById":144343,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T07:43:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, so I couldn\u0027t quite get it in one take... but here\u0027s the Harrier-styled Jump Jet I made, thanks to TCA and Mk2 Stockalike Expansion\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/YN7Na1pKf9s?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222814146\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002297154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476949355\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002299885\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022allista\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, allista said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is another hard-to-explain design decisions: manual engines may be controlled manually, unless you use some sort of horizontal speed control (or autopilots that use it). For example, the Stop\u00A0program will\u00A0use manual engines; the Cruise, Path Navigation... anything that controls horizontal movement. So \u0022manual\u0022 engines are not so manual after all\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut, if you say that Vertical Speed/Altitude\u00A0Control has something to do, that it\u0027s probably a bug. It shouldn\u0027t.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll investigate the matter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm... well I\u0027m not 100% sure I was -only- using vertical speed control. I may have had \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E assist and/or Level on. Would either of those keep it from working?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"allista","CreatedById":99885,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T07:52:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222814148\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002297154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476949425\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144343\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FirroSeranel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, FirroSeranel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm... well I\u0027m not 100% sure I was -only- using vertical speed control. I may have had \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E assist and/or Level on. Would either of those keep it from working?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E Assist -- yes,\u00A0it explicitly\u00A0uses Stop.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLevel -- no, it only uses attitude control.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FirroSeranel","CreatedById":144343,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T07:58:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, I\u0027ll try it again without \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E assist.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"allista","CreatedById":99885,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T08:11:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222814157\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002297154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476950296\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144343\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FirroSeranel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, FirroSeranel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, I\u0027ll try it again without \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E assist.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E assist uses Stop explicitly: it pushes the button for you as soon as you took off to steady the craft. You can push it yourself again afterwards to disable. No need to disable the whole assist program.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FirroSeranel","CreatedById":144343,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T08:14:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222814163\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002297154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476951070\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002299885\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022allista\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, allista said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E assist uses Stop explicitly: it pushes the button for you as soon as you took off to steady the craft. You can push it yourself again afterwards to disable. No need to disable the whole assist program.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat else does it do, exactly? I know that with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E Mode, ships act kind of like GTA-style helicopters, and with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E Assist they act a bit more like a RL helicopter with a good flight instructor along for the ride...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre those just combinations of modes that you assigned a name and button to? Or do they have something more going on behind the scenes?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"allista","CreatedById":99885,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T08:40:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222814165\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002297154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476951240\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144343\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FirroSeranel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, FirroSeranel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat else does it do, exactly? I know that with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E Mode, ships act kind of like GTA-style helicopters, and with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E Assist they act a bit more like a RL helicopter with a good flight instructor along for the ride...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre those just combinations of modes that you assigned a name and button to? Or do they have something more going on behind the scenes?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNah, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E Assist is just this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nwhen you land vertically, it automatically extends landing gear, and when you touch-down, it tries to steady the ship using pitch-yaw-roll controls and whatever torque the ship has.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nwhen you take off vertically, before you actually took off (engines working, but there\u0027s not enough thrust yet) it also tries to steady the ship; when you finally took off, it pushes the \u0022Stop\u0022 button to kill horizontal speed and retracts landing gear.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nin any other situation it does nothing.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"allista","CreatedById":99885,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T09:02:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222814148\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002297154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476949425\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144343\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FirroSeranel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, FirroSeranel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm... well I\u0027m not 100% sure I was -only- using vertical speed control. I may have had \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E assist and/or Level on. Would either of those keep it from working?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve tested things and this is definitely a bug\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:huh:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_undecided.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:huh:\u0022\u003E\u00A0Thanks for the report!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bit Fiddler","CreatedById":103108,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T09:15:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis one seems to work great\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Screenshot%202016-10-20%2018.14.48.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/75023494/Screenshot%202016-10-20%2018.14.48.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"allista","CreatedById":99885,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T09:19:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222814220\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002297154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476954952\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103108\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bit Fiddler\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Bit Fiddler said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis one seems to work great\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/75023494/Screenshot%202016-10-20%2018.14.48.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Screenshot%202016-10-20%2018.14.48.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/75023494/Screenshot%202016-10-20%2018.14.48.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow come the G1 is set to Off, but works?!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bit Fiddler","CreatedById":103108,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T09:20:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\noh it pulses on and off\u00A0 screenie just got it at wrong time\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/sh/rx7v18ucz6wjut4/AACbJ4nOG3sc1CjBrNL_wtowa?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/sh/rx7v18ucz6wjut4/AACbJ4nOG3sc1CjBrNL_wtowa?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-20T09:25:52Z\u0022 title=\u002210/20/2016 09:25  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 20, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Bit Fiddler\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"allista","CreatedById":99885,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T09:24:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222814227\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002297154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476955242\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103108\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bit Fiddler\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Bit Fiddler said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\noh it pulses on and off\u00A0 screenie just got it at wrong time\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt pulses?!?!?!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:0.0:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_shocked.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:0.0:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs someone rewriting my code while I sleep?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh boy... another bug\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;.;\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cry.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;.;\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bit Fiddler","CreatedById":103108,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T09:29:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwell not sure it is a bug...\u00A0 it flies like a dream\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\njust burns a metric excrements ton of fuel...\u00A0\u00A0 but my prop design was not working so well....\u00A0 have to go try it again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nok was just a kerbalmoment I guess...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis one works great as well\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Screenshot%202016-10-20%2018.34.20.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/75023494/VTOL%20TEST/Screenshot%202016-10-20%2018.34.20.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthese are great designs as the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E fans are EC only they do not use any fuel.\u00A0 so the rear engine produces EC that in turn powers the ducted fans and a few intake air \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E jets for some extra stability control.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-20T09:38:48Z\u0022 title=\u002210/20/2016 09:38  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 20, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Bit Fiddler\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Denko666","CreatedById":135673,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T11:49:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/99885-allista/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002299885\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/99885-allista/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@allista\u003C/a\u003E! I tried what you said about toggling TCA together with the engines to switch between different plane modes, and it works! Really well actually... have a gander at this photoalbum of my most recent attempt to get to Duna:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://flic.kr/s/aHskFCVmjm\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://flic.kr/s/aHskFCVmjm\u003C/a\u003E. The spaceplane enters Duna\u0027s atmosphere like NASA\u0027s shuttle, using its entire lifting body as a brake. Then flies\u00A0down further as a plane before eventually switching to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E mode to find an acceptable landing spot. Deliver the Rover and crew, then take off again into orbit, back to the interplanetary stage to get the rest of the equipment. Wonderful!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"allista","CreatedById":99885,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T11:54:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222814348\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002297154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476964171\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022135673\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Denko666\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Denko666 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/99885-allista/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002299885\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/99885-allista/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@allista\u003C/a\u003E! I tried what you said about toggling TCA together with the engines to switch between different plane modes, and it works! Really well actually... have a gander at this photoalbum of my most recent attempt to get to Duna:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://flic.kr/s/aHskFCVmjm\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://flic.kr/s/aHskFCVmjm\u003C/a\u003E. The spaceplane enters Duna\u0027s atmosphere like NASA\u0027s shuttle, using its entire lifting body as a brake. Then flies\u00A0down further as a plane before eventually switching to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E mode to find an acceptable landing spot. Deliver the Rover and crew, then take off again into orbit, back to the interplanetary stage to get the rest of the equipment. Wonderful!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bit Fiddler","CreatedById":103108,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T11:55:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\noh hey what is that space plane part pack I have been looking for that for months but cant remember what it is called\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Denko666","CreatedById":135673,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T12:17:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222814354\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002297154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476964522\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103108\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bit Fiddler\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Bit Fiddler said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\noh hey what is that space plane part pack I have been looking for that for months but cant remember what it is called\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s \u003Ca href=\u0022http://spacedock.info/mod/711/Orbit%20Portal%20Technology%20%5BOPT%5D%20Spaceplane%20Parts\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EOrbit Portal Technology (OPT)\u003C/a\u003E. maintained by K.Yeon current version has been made KSP 1.2 compatible (v1.8.6) and the K.Yeon plans to have 1.9 ready by end this month with some very exciting changes and new stuff! That,\u003Ca href=\u0022http://spacedock.info/mod/668/%20Radial%20Engine%20for%20spacecraft%20-%20T.G.O.L%20group%20\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E T.G.O.L. Small Radial \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E engines\u003C/a\u003E and the \u003Ca href=\u0022http://spacedock.info/mod/473/Mk2%20Stockalike%20Expansion\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EmkII Expansion\u003C/a\u003E is what i always use for spaceplanes. I wouldn\u0027t want to build one without them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Talavar","CreatedById":75264,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T13:16:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00221679414\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002297154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221422226579\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002299885\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022allista\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/25/2015 at 5:56 PM, allista said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Allista, did you write an entirely new navigation system, or is this just mechjeb\u0027s code being enhanced? because I gotta say..\u00A0 while I like mechjeb and wouldn\u0027t knock the use I get out of it..., these videos of TCA\u0027s maneuver capabilities are making Mechjeb look like hammered S**t. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:0.0:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_shocked.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:0.0:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-20T13:17:44Z\u0022 title=\u002210/20/2016 01:17  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 20, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Talavar\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"allista","CreatedById":99885,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T13:20:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222813817\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002297154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476928669\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144343\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FirroSeranel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, FirroSeranel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/99885-allista/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002299885\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/99885-allista/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@allista\u003C/a\u003E, I have another request.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would like the ability to have a macro trigger an action group. I have mods with engines that can switch from hover to flight mode, like the Harrier, but no way to trigger the transition as part of a macro. Would this be difficult to add?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDone. Added two macros: \u003Cstrong\u003EToggle Action Groups\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003ESet Action Groups\u003C/strong\u003E. Both allow you to\u00A0control many action groups at once. The first only toggles the ones you have selected. The second sets all of them: enables the ones you have selected and\u00A0disables the others.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"allista","CreatedById":99885,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T13:30:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222814423\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002297154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476969405\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002275264\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Talavar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Talavar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Allista, did you write an entirely new navigation system, or is this just mechjeb\u0027s code being enhanced? because I gotta say..\u00A0 while I like mechjeb and wouldn\u0027t knock the use I get out of it..., these videos of TCA\u0027s maneuver capabilities are making Mechjeb look like hammered S**t. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:0.0:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_shocked.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:0.0:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWll, all the high-level staff: the navigation, maneuvering and autopilots are written from scratch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did, however,\u00A0took several things from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E: it\u0027s code for inertia tensor calculation, inertia correction for\u00A0attitude control, one of its PID controller implementations and several other minor things. Most\u00A0of which has been more or less\u00A0rewritten over the time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Talavar","CreatedById":75264,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-20T18:50:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222814446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002297154\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476970232\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002299885\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022allista\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, allista said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWll, all the high-level staff: the navigation, maneuvering and autopilots are written from scratch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did, however,\u00A0took several things from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E: it\u0027s code for inertia tensor calculation, inertia correction for\u00A0attitude control, one of its PID controller implementations and several other minor things. Most\u00A0of which has been more or less\u00A0rewritten over the time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Been playing with it for over an hour now.. MASSIVE improvement over \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E. Thanks a million, man. Great work you\u0027re doing!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}